WEBVTT

00:00.600 --> 00:02.735
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:25.925 --> 00:29.294
>> This pie chart is an
illustration of the composition
of happiness.

00:29.296 --> 00:33.932
This portion here represents the
ratio of love needed in one's
life.

00:33.934 --> 00:37.336
This portion here is the...
[ Garbled ]
>> Gumball: Hmm.

00:37.338 --> 00:41.473
My brain is amazing.
When i find something boring, it
actually prevents me from

00:41.475 --> 00:45.277
hearing it.
>> [ Garbled ]
>> Darwin: Hmm, i don't think

00:45.279 --> 00:48.881
it's your brain.
I think it's his.
He should seriously give up on

00:48.883 --> 00:52.151
this herbal tea.
>> [ Gasps ]
...And this portion represents

00:52.153 --> 00:55.454
the amount --
[ Bell ringing ]
Class displ--

00:55.456 --> 00:59.358
[ thud ]
>> Thanks for the pen, dude.
>> Darwin: No problem.

00:59.360 --> 01:03.362
[ Whip! ]
>> Gumball: Hmm.
Hey!

01:03.364 --> 01:20.546
>> What?
Eh, eh, eh, ah, ah, ah.
>> Gumball: What the durf is

01:20.548 --> 01:22.915
that?
>> I don't know.
What are<i> you</i> doing?

01:22.917 --> 01:27.119
>> Gumball: The pen!
You chewed his pen!
>> No, i didn't.

01:27.121 --> 01:30.322
>> Gumball: Aah!
Can you believe this guy?
>> Darwin: Relax, dude.

01:30.324 --> 01:33.092
It's only a pen.
>> Gumball: don't you "dude" me
when I'm right!

01:33.094 --> 01:36.929
You're supposed to chew things
you eat, not people's stuff!
>> Darwin: What about gum?

01:36.931 --> 01:39.731
>> Gumball: What about it?
>> Darwin: You don't eat gum,
but you chew that.

01:39.733 --> 01:42.534
It's even in the name -- chewing
gum.
>> Gumball: Yeah, sure, but

01:42.536 --> 01:46.038
that's specifically made for
chewing.
That wasn't a chewing pen.

01:46.040 --> 01:48.373
You write with a pen!
>> Darwin: You can get a
fountain pen.

01:48.375 --> 01:51.710
You don't spray water with it.
>> Gumball: You just don't chew
other people's pens!

01:51.712 --> 01:58.383
It's the principle!
This is what society is built
upon -- respect!

01:58.385 --> 02:02.588
[ Sighs ]
You know, there's nothing that
can't be solved with an apology,

02:02.590 --> 02:05.958
Joe.
>> Hmm.
I forgive you for accusing me of

02:05.960 --> 02:10.562
chewing the pen.
>> Gumball: [ Inhales sharply ]
Can i borrow your glue, please?

02:10.564 --> 02:14.133
>> Yes, of course.
But don't go chewing on it.
[ Laughs ]

02:14.135 --> 02:21.039
>> Gumball: [ Laughs ]
>> Darwin: What are you doing?
>> Gumball: Exacting justice.

02:21.041 --> 02:24.576
>> Darwin: What kind of justice
is piercing the tube of glue
like a psycho?

02:24.578 --> 02:28.013
>> Gumball: [ Sighs ]
[ Whap! ]
>> Darwin: Ow!

02:28.015 --> 02:30.682
>> Gumball: Now, what do you
feel is an appropriate thing to
do in return?

02:30.684 --> 02:33.552
>> Darwin: Turn the other cheek.
>> Gumball: Which means i can do
this.

02:33.554 --> 02:36.255
[ Whap! ]
>> Darwin: Ooh!
>> Gumball: That emotion you're

02:36.257 --> 02:39.158
feeling is your thirst for
justice.
Quench it!

02:39.160 --> 02:44.596
>> Darwin: But what if you offer
love instead of hatred?
>> Gumball: Oh, yeah.

02:44.598 --> 02:48.066
That is nicer.
But it's not justice!
This is justice!

02:48.068 --> 02:54.406
This is justice!
This is justice!
>> [ Whistling ]

02:54.408 --> 03:00.412
"Thanks for the glue."
Aww. How swell.
I should make them a card to

03:00.414 --> 03:05.617
celebrate our friendship.
[ Marker squeaking ]
[ Humming ]

03:05.619 --> 03:09.821
Ah.
[ Rattling ]
Gee!

03:09.823 --> 03:13.625
That's what i call a sticky
situation.
[ Laughs ]

03:13.627 --> 03:18.197
Whoopsie!
[ Laughs ]
[ Grunts ]

03:18.199 --> 03:23.435
Oh. Darwin's homework.
[ Chuckling ] Well, what am i
gonna<i> glue</i> now?

03:23.437 --> 03:29.241
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]
Looks like I'm getting more and

03:29.243 --> 03:33.845
more attached to this school.
[ Laughs ]
[ Groans ]

03:33.847 --> 03:37.316
Now I'm even bonding with
myself.
[ Laughs ]

03:37.318 --> 03:42.154
[ Grunting ]
[ Laughs ]
[ Whimpers ]

03:42.156 --> 03:46.658
Aaaah!
>> Okay, Joe, we're going to
take the bandages off now, but i

03:46.660 --> 03:50.662
just want to warn you that,
well, we did the best we could.

04:07.513 --> 04:13.752
>> Aaaaaaaaah!
Oh. It's not so bad.
>> We found this tube of glue

04:13.754 --> 04:17.889
stuck to your, uh...Anyway, in
future, you need to be more
careful.

04:17.891 --> 04:22.461
This tube was covered in holes.
>> But it wasn't when i lent it
to gumball.

04:22.463 --> 04:28.100
>> Hmm.
>> Hmm.
>> Hmm.

04:28.102 --> 04:32.738
Oh, come on!
>> Gumball: I can understand the
glue, but why the glitter?

04:32.740 --> 04:36.408
Like putting lipstick on a
skeleton.
It doesn't make it any nicer.

04:36.410 --> 04:40.145
Eh, you were right.
We should have let that pen
stuff slide.

04:40.147 --> 04:49.187
>> Darwin: [ Breathing deeply ]
>> Gumball: Dude, please chill
out!

04:49.189 --> 04:55.160
Here, have some love.
>> Darwin: This -- this is for
my homework!

04:55.162 --> 05:02.501
And this is for the glitter!
[ Squeaking ]
>> Gumball: Just pop it already!

05:02.503 --> 05:05.170
[ Bang! ]
Aaaah!
>> Darwin: He destroyed your

05:05.172 --> 05:14.179
desk, too, so chew on this!
>> Gumball: [ Growling ]
That's for my desk that i don't

05:14.181 --> 05:18.817
really care about that much!
[ Growls ] Take that, you
banana!

05:18.819 --> 05:23.155
>> Darwin: Oh, look.
A pen!
And it's not chewed!

05:23.157 --> 05:30.228
[ Growling ]
What else can we do to it?
>><i> Attention please.</i>

05:30.230 --> 05:33.231
<i>Could gumball and</i>
<i>Darwin watterson please come to</i>
<i>Mr. small's office?</i>

05:33.233 --> 05:40.872
<i>Thank you very much.</i>
[ Chuckles ]
>> [ Chuckles ]

05:40.874 --> 05:45.610
>> [ Clears throat ]
Any conflict can be resolved
with these three tools.

05:45.612 --> 05:50.849
The mirror reminds us that an
enemy is just ourselves but seen
from another angle.

05:50.851 --> 05:56.388
The water reminds us that we all
have something in common.
And the hourglass is the time we

05:56.390 --> 06:04.596
need to reach an understanding.
Aaah!
>> Aaah!

06:04.598 --> 06:06.631
Aaah!
>> Darwin: Come on, you
googley-eyed punk!

06:06.633 --> 06:09.401
>> Gumball: Darwin!
>> Darwin: We got one minute.
Let's finish this.

06:09.403 --> 06:14.306
>> Geez, Louise!
The pen! Give him the new pen!
>> [ Whimpers ]

06:14.308 --> 06:17.809
I didn't chew your pen,
honestly.
But i bought you a new one

06:17.811 --> 06:22.214
because i, myself, have a pen of
great sentimental value.
>> Gumball: [ Laughs ]

06:22.216 --> 06:26.918
It's not a fountain pen, is it?
>> Actually, yes, it is.
[ Both whimper ]

06:26.920 --> 06:30.989
It's the pen that
obadiah banana, the founder of
our family, used to sign the

06:30.991 --> 06:34.259
registry when he first came to
this country.
[ Both whimper ]

06:34.261 --> 06:38.697
It was a very expensive pen.
I'm not even gonna tell you
where he had to hide it to keep

06:38.699 --> 06:40.999
it safe.
[ Laughs ]
>> Darwin: [ Gags ]

06:41.001 --> 06:45.637
>> I would lose my mind if
anyone chewed on<i> that</i> pen!
Anyway, please accept this new

06:45.639 --> 06:50.876
pen, and let's be friends again.
>> Aww.
>> Eh?

06:50.878 --> 06:54.346
>> Gumball: Dude, we have to get
to his locker before he sees
what we've done.

06:54.348 --> 06:56.915
>> Darwin: Thank you.
We've got to go now. Bye.
>> One minute.

06:56.917 --> 07:00.252
Thank you for a beautiful
resolution.
Banana Joe, you can go.

07:00.254 --> 07:03.855
I just need to fill out your
hall pass, guys.
[ Door opens, closes ]

07:03.857 --> 07:07.426
Gu-u-mba-a-ll.
[ Chuckles ] That's a funny
name, isn't it?

07:07.428 --> 07:11.062
Now, do you spell it with two or
three l's?
>> Gumball: Two. Two l's.

07:11.064 --> 07:13.665
>> [ Chuckles ]
I'm sorry. I just put one.
>> Darwin: Dude!

07:13.667 --> 07:17.269
You could have just put another
one at the end!
>> Of course.

07:17.271 --> 07:20.872
Silly old hippie.
I'll do another one.
Oh, wait. I'm all out.

07:20.874 --> 07:24.342
Uh, I'll to print one.
>> Gumball: Come on!
>> Huh?

07:24.344 --> 07:29.047
>> Darwin: Just print it please!
>> Yeah, sure.
Here it is!

07:29.049 --> 07:35.587
Old reliable.
[ Both coughing ]
I don't know how it works.

07:35.589 --> 07:39.758
>> Gumball: Just let us go,
okay?!
>> You seem a little stressed

07:39.760 --> 07:42.994
out, guys.
You want to try my herbal
infusion?

07:42.996 --> 07:50.602
[ Slurps ]
It's very good for the nerv...
>> Gumball: Mr. small?

07:50.604 --> 07:55.340
>> Darwin: Yo!
>> Gumball: Right. Come on.
[ Door opens, closes ]

07:55.342 --> 08:02.781
>> Whooooo-hoo!
>> [ Whistling ]

08:09.388 --> 08:21.333
>> [ Slurps ]
[ Whistling slows ]
[ Whistling stops ]

08:42.154 --> 08:46.791
>> Hey!
Turn around, you cowards.
>> Gumball: [ Chuckles

08:46.793 --> 08:49.160
nervously ]
No, thank you.
>> Turn around and face the can

08:49.162 --> 08:52.831
of butt-whupping that I'm gonna
open on you!
>> Darwin: Wouldn't it be better

08:52.833 --> 08:58.470
to stay like we are for that?
>> Turn around!!
>> Darwin: Should we turn

08:58.472 --> 09:01.172
around?
>> Gumball: I don't want to turn
around.

09:01.174 --> 09:11.416
>> Both: [ Inhale deeply ]
>> Gumball: Okay.
>> Aaaaaah!

09:11.418 --> 09:18.590
[ Clang! ]
[ Groans ]
>> Gumball: Oh, that's just

09:18.592 --> 09:22.160
great!
Now people are gonna come around
the corner, see him like that,

09:22.162 --> 09:26.431
and think we're massive bullies!
>> Darwin: Which we are!!
Because of us, he lost an eye,

09:26.433 --> 09:30.602
and we attacked him with a
mirror, we punctured his tube of
glue, we chewed everything in

09:30.604 --> 09:34.806
his locker, he got a huge brown
banana bruise on his little
face, and we even managed to

09:34.808 --> 09:38.443
ruin the most precious thing his
family ever owned!
>> Gumball: [ Cries ]

09:38.445 --> 09:42.447
He did chew that pen, though.
>> Darwin: It doesn't matter!!
What are we gonna do now?!

09:42.449 --> 09:46.685
>> Gumball: [ Grunting ]
>> Darwin: What are you doing?
>> Gumball: We need to make it

09:46.687 --> 09:50.589
look like he won the fight.
>> Darwin: [ Gasps ]
And then we'll be even and we

09:50.591 --> 09:59.097
can be friends again and no one
will ever know what horrible
people we are.

09:59.099 --> 10:04.002
>> Gumball: Banana Joe, please!
Not the face!
>> Darwin: On, no!

10:04.004 --> 10:11.810
Not with the elbow!
>> Both: [ Laughing ]
>> Gumball: Hey, pull one of my

10:11.812 --> 10:14.946
teeth out.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
That's completely over the top,

10:14.948 --> 10:20.485
isn't it?
Let's just get into position.
>> [ Groans ]

10:20.487 --> 10:23.655
What happened?
>> Gumball: [ Groans ]
You kicked our butts like a

10:23.657 --> 10:26.091
beast.
That's what happened.
>> Awesome.

10:26.093 --> 10:30.261
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
I mean, I'm sorry.
How did it ever come to this?

10:30.263 --> 10:34.699
>> Darwin: It's our fault, Joe.
We didn't know it was your
family pen.

10:34.701 --> 10:40.538
>> Well, obadiah banana always
said that nothing is lost until
you lose a friend, and i don't

10:40.540 --> 10:44.776
want that to happen to us.
>> Gumball: [ Cries ]
That's really lame.

10:44.778 --> 10:49.881
>> Darwin: Group hug?
>> Ahh.
[ All groaning ]

10:49.883 --> 10:52.651
>> Gumball: [ Gasps ]
Ow!
What is that?

10:52.653 --> 10:55.553
Oh.
Hey, Darwin, here's your pen.
>> Darwin: What?

10:55.555 --> 10:58.123
>> Gumball: Your pen. Look.
It's got your initials on it.
Wait.

10:58.125 --> 11:03.094
[ Chuckling ] Oh, man.
You know what this means?
It means the pen you lent Joe

11:03.096 --> 11:07.666
was my pen, not yours, and i was
the one who chewed it.
I always chew my pen!

11:07.668 --> 11:11.102
Ha-ha!
[Laughing] Isn't that funny?
All this fighting for nothing,

11:11.104 --> 11:16.307
when i had the pen in my pocket
the whole time.
Pretty fun, huh, guys?

11:16.309 --> 11:18.510
Guys?

12:01.520 --> 12:04.789
[ Dishes clattering ]
>> Gumball: ¶ tonight is going
to be awesome ¶

12:04.791 --> 12:07.992
i can't believe they're going to
show it!
>> Darwin: TV is finally gonna

12:07.994 --> 12:10.929
acknowledge our existence.
>> Anais: What are you talking
about?

12:10.931 --> 12:13.732
>> Darwin: Only "cutey pets."
>> Gumball: The number-one pet
show on TV.

12:13.734 --> 12:16.935
>> Darwin: They're gonna show
this photo!
>> Anais: But i thought you

12:16.937 --> 12:20.805
preferred "animal companions"?
>> Darwin: Aw, who cares about
moral principles?

12:20.807 --> 12:25.577
